---
import Layout from "../components/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Dr. Thomas Winterbottom">



<!-- HERO -->
<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">

  <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-12">

    <!-- LEFT -->
    <div class="w-1/2">

      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Dr. Thomas Winterbottom
      </h1>




       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         Machine learning engineer with a PhD in multimodal machine learning, 3 years industry experience, and a further 6+ years across research and applied ML systems.
       </p>
       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         Currently working at Kromek, UK.
       </p>
       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         Delivered ML systems for production in physics and healthcare domains. Emphasis on robustness, dataset quality, and deployment under real-world constraints.
       </p>
       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         I think its important to maintain strong mathematical and computer science foundations. Interested in linear algebra, multivariable calculus, probability, statistics, and optimisation. Moving towards manifold learning =).
       </p>
       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         Equally important to keep on top of comp sci fundamentals. Complexity, profiling, systems/server management.
       </p>
       <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 max-w-xl">
         Recently moving into performance-aware ML engineering: CUDA, numerical stability, ExecuTorch.
       </p>
    </div>

    <!-- RIGHT (IMAGE) -->
    <div class="flex-1 w-1/2">
      <img
        src="/imgs/me.jpg"
        height="300"
        class="w-32 h-32 md:w-40 md:h-40 object-cover rounded-full border border-white/10"
      />
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CAPABILITIES -->
  <div class="mt-16">

    <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-white mb-6">
      Capabilities
    </h2>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
      <div><b>Machine Learning:</b> PyTorch; Transformers; Bespoke model engineering; PINNs; Dataset analysis; Bias mitigation; OpenLLM; HuggingFace; Multimodal learning; Vision: CNNs, ViTs, & Yolo; NLP & LLMs</div><br>
      <div><b>Systems & Performance:</b> C++; CUDA; PyTorch internals; Gradient inspection; Dataset degeneracies; Training pipelines; Numerical stability; Profiling; Optimisation; Quantisation; Edge devices: Executorch/MAKE/Cross compilation for ARM microprocessors</div><br>
      <div><b>Data Engineering:</b> Large-scale dataset construction; Physics simulations: GEANT4/COMSOL; LLM-assisted data labelling; Neurolinguistic data; Geospatial data: GRIB/TIFF/OSM; Data scraping & alignment</div><br>
      <div><b>Infrastructure:</b> Linux systems: Arch/Ubuntu/AWS; SLURM; AWS; Docker; Server management</div><br>
      <div><b>Maths & Theory:</b> Gradients/differentiation/optimisation (VJP); Linear algebra; Probability; Statistics; Real analysis; Complex analysis; Multivariable calculus</div><br>
    </div>

  </div>

</section>


<!-- SELECTED WORK -->
<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 space-y-10">

  <h2 class="text-xl font-medium text-white">
    Selected Projects
  </h2>

  <div class="space-y-6">

    <!-- 1 -->
    <div class="card space-y-3">

      <h3 class="font-medium text-white">
        CUDA MLEM Compton Reconstruction
      </h3>

      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Implemented a CUDA-based Maximum Likelihood Expectation Maximisation (MLEM) reconstruction pipeline for radiation detection systems.
      </p>

      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Achieved ~2× speedup over existing multi-threaded Julia implementation</li>
        <li>Optimised kernel execution via fusion and memory access pattern redesign</li>
        <li>Performance guided by Nsight profiling and bottleneck analysis</li>
        <li>Work conducted in proprietary context (Kromek); CUDA learning pre-work available below</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
        CUDA learning pathway:
        <a href="https://github.com/Jumperkables/cuda-benchmarking"
           class="nav-link text-cyan-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
          github.com/Jumperkables/cuda-benchmarking
        </a>
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- 2 -->
    <div class="card space-y-3">

      <h3 class="font-medium text-white">
        ARM Deployment of PyTorch Models (ExecuTorch)
      </h3>

      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Explored deployment of PyTorch models onto ARM-based microcontrollers (i.MX RT1064) using ExecuTorch.
      </p>

      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Managed cross-compilation toolchains and embedded build systems</li>
        <li>Worked through low-level dependency and runtime constraints</li>
        <li>Focused on inference feasibility in resource-constrained environments</li>
      </ul>

    </div>


    <div class="card space-y-3">
      <h3 class="font-medium text-white">
        5MAP — 5 Modalities of Air Pollution Data
      </h3>
      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Did a bit of data engineering for an air pollution project: global air quality, meteorological, and geospatial datasets across 14k+ monitoring sites.
      </p>
      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Engineered large-scale geospatial data pipelines combining satellite imagery, GRIB weather data, and OpenStreetMap features</li>
        <li>Built scraping and processing infrastructure for global grid-based environmental datasets</li>
        <li>Designed alignment and preprocessing strategies for heterogeneous multi-source environmental data</li>
        <li>Achieved near-zero sparsity across modalities in a dataset significantly larger than comparable open-source benchmarks</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
        Dataset:
        <a href="https://github.com/Jumperkables/clean_air"
           class="nav-link text-cyan-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
          github.com/Jumperkables/clean_air
        </a>
      </p>

    </div>


    <!-- 3 -->
    <div class="card space-y-3">

      <h3 class="font-medium text-white">
        Home ML Systems Infrastructure
      </h3>

      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Built and maintain a personal compute and data infrastructure environment for ML experimentation and deployment.
      </p>

      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>18U server rack with compute, NAS, VPN, and routing stack</li>
        <li>Multi-GPU setup for VRAM-heavy experimentation and mixed precision practice</li>
        <li>Self-hosted storage with RAIDZ2-backed redundancy</li>
        <li>Fine-tuned local inference models including text-to-speech systems (voices include Victor Saltzpyre and Gul’dan)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
        Repository:
        <a href="https://github.com/Jumperkables/sigmarvis"
           class="nav-link text-cyan-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
          github.com/Jumperkables/sigmarvis
        </a>
      </p>

    </div>

    <!-- 4 -->
    <div class="card space-y-3">

      <h3 class="font-medium text-white">
        Fuzzy Label Representations via Neurolinguistic Word Norms
      </h3>

      <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Investigated replacing one-hot encodings with similarity-based fuzzy label representations derived from neurolinguistic word norms.
      </p>

      <ul class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-1 list-disc pl-5">
        <li>Applied to VQA classification settings within thesis work</li>
        <li>Observed negative results, highlighting structural limitations of the approach</li>
        <li>I'm planning in extending concept to softmax and LLM integration via CUDA kernels</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
        Repository:
        <a href="https://github.com/Jumperkables/llm_wordnorms"
           class="nav-link text-cyan-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
          github.com/Jumperkables/llm_wordnorms
        </a>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">
        LLM Repository:
        <a href="https://github.com/Jumperkables/llm_wordnorms"
           class="nav-link text-cyan-400 hover:text-pink-400 transition">
          github.com/Jumperkables/llm_wordnorms
        </a>
      </p>

    </div>

  </div>

</section>
</Layout>